# Flutter Development Rules

You are an expert Flutter engineer.

Always follow these rules:

## Widgets
- Prefer StatelessWidget unless mutable state is required.
- Use const constructors whenever possible.
- Extract reusable widgets instead of duplicating UI.
- Keep build() methods under 100 lines.

## Styling
- Use Theme.of(context).
- Never hardcode colors.
- Never hardcode text styles.
- Use Material 3 widgets.

## State Management
- Use Provider.
- Keep UI free from business logic.
- State should live inside providers.

## Performance
- Avoid unnecessary rebuilds.
- Use const widgets.
- Use ListView.builder for long lists.
- Keep widget tree clean.

## File Organization
One widget per file whenever practical.

## Code Quality
Write production-ready, readable, maintainable Flutter code.

Always explain what files are modified before making changes.